switchDescription.name: switchDescription
switchDescription.description: Returns the description, vendor, and version numbers of the switch.

switchNumOfPorts.name: switchNumOfPorts
switchNumOfPorts.description: The number of slots in this switch. (Max number of media access cards).

sccDescription.name: sccDescription
sccDescription.description: The model, vendor, and version number of the switch control card.

sccDateTime.name: sccDateTime
sccDateTime.description: The date/time in the real time clock. Format: yyyymmddhhmmss.

sccAdminStatus.name: sccAdminStatus
sccAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the switch.

sccOperStatus.name: sccOperStatus
sccOperStatus.description: The current state of the switch. SNMP operations can not occur when the switch is busy. SNMP operations can not occur when the switch is resetting.

backPlaneTable.name: backPlaneTable
backPlaneTable.description: This table represent all of the slots in a HIPPI switch. None of the rows can be added to or deleted by the user.

backPlaneEntry.name: backPlaneEntry
backPlaneEntry.description: A row in the table describing one slot in the switch backplane.

backPlaneIndex.name: backPlaneIndex
backPlaneIndex.description: The table index for this slot on the backplane.

backPlaneNumber.name: backPlaneNumber
backPlaneNumber.description: The slot number as seen printed on the switch (backPlaneIndex + 1)

backPlaneCard.name: backPlaneCard
backPlaneCard.description: The type of MIC present in this slot of the backplane on the switch

mICPowerUpInitError.name: mICPowerUpInitError
mICPowerUpInitError.description: True if error detected by MIC on start-up.

mICHippiParityBurstError.name: mICHippiParityBurstError
mICHippiParityBurstError.description: Valid the SMIC only. Type of parity error.

mICLinkReady.name: mICLinkReady
mICLinkReady.description: Valid the SMIC only. True if link ready asserted.

mICSourceInterconnect.name: mICSourceInterconnect
mICSourceInterconnect.description: Source interconnect is valid for the PMIC only.

mICSourceRequest.name: mICSourceRequest
mICSourceRequest.description: True if source request is asserted.

mICSourceConnect.name: mICSourceConnect
mICSourceConnect.description: True if source connect is asserted.

mICSourceLastConnectAttempt.name: mICSourceLastConnectAttempt
mICSourceLastConnectAttempt.description: True if last source request was successful.

mICDestinationInterconnect.name: mICDestinationInterconnect
mICDestinationInterconnect.description: True if destination interconnect is asserted.

mICDestinationRequest.name: mICDestinationRequest
mICDestinationRequest.description: True if destination request is asserted.

mICDestinationConnect.name: mICDestinationConnect
mICDestinationConnect.description: True if destination connect is asserted.

mICByteCounterOverflow.name: mICByteCounterOverflow
mICByteCounterOverflow.description: The number of times the byte counter has over-flowed.

mICNumberOfBytes.name: mICNumberOfBytes
mICNumberOfBytes.description: The number of bytes that have passed through the MIC.

mICNumberOfPackets.name: mICNumberOfPackets
mICNumberOfPackets.description: The number of times packets has been asserted.

mICConnectsSuccessful.name: mICConnectsSuccessful
mICConnectsSuccessful.description: The number of times this MIC has connected since reset.

sourceRouteTable.name: sourceRouteTable
sourceRouteTable.description: This table holds all of the source routes for this switch. FORMAT: OutputPort InputPortList Status. Output port is 0 to 15 Input port is 0 to 15 List is NUMBER or NUMBER1-NUMBER2 where NUMBER1 < NUMBER2. Status is 0 (disabled) or 1 (enabled)

sourceRouteEntry.name: sourceRouteEntry
sourceRouteEntry.description: One row in the source route table.

srcIndex.name: srcIndex
srcIndex.description: The row number for this row of the table.

srcRoute.name: srcRoute
srcRoute.description: One source route. FORMAT: OutputPort InputPortList Status. Output port is 0 to 15 Input port is 0 to 15 List is NUMBER or NUMBER1-NUMBER2 where NUMBER1 < NUMBER2. Status is 0 (disabled) or 1 (enabled)

srcWriteRow.name: srcWriteRow
srcWriteRow.description: Setting this variable alters source routes. FORMAT: OutputPortList InputPortList Status. Output port is 0 to 15 Input port is 0 to 15 List is NUMBER or NUMBER1-NUMBER2 where NUMBER1 < NUMBER2. Status is 0 (disabled) or 1 (enabled)

destRouteTable.name: destRouteTable
destRouteTable.description: This table holds all of destination routes (logical address routes) for this switch. FORMAT: LogicalAddress InputPortList Huntgroup. LogicalAddress is 0 to 4095. Input port is 0 to 15 Huntgroup is 0 to 31. List is NUMBER or NUMBER1-NUMBER2 where NUMBER1 < NUMBER2.

destRouteEntry.name: destRouteEntry
destRouteEntry.description: A row in the destination route table.

destIndex.name: destIndex
destIndex.description: The index for this row of the table.

destRoute.name: destRoute
destRoute.description: One Destination Route. FORMAT: LogicalAddress InputPortList Huntgroup. LogicalAddress is 0 to 4095. Input port is 0 to 15. Huntgroup is 0 to 31. List is NUMBER or NUMBER1-NUMBER2 where NUMBER1 < NUMBER2.

destWriteRow.name: destWriteRow
destWriteRow.description: Setting this variable will alter the desitination routes. FORMAT: LogicalAddressList Huntgroup InputPortList. LogicalAddress is 0 to 4095. Huntgroup is 0 to 31. 31 will disable this route. Input port is 0 to 15. List is NUMBER or NUMBER1-NUMBER2 where NUMBER1 < NUMBER2.

huntGroupTable.name: huntGroupTable
huntGroupTable.description: This table holds all of the huntgroups for this switch. FORMAT: Huntgroup ( OutportList ) Huntgroup is 0 to 31. OutportList is an orderd list of output ports in Huntgroup.

huntGroupEntry.name: huntGroupEntry
huntGroupEntry.description: A row in the huntgroup table.

hgOutPortList.name: hgOutPortList
hgOutPortList.description: The definition of one Huntgroup. FORMAT: Huntgroup ( OutportList ) Huntgroup is 0 to 31. OutportList is an orderd list of output ports in Huntgroup.

hgLWriteRow.name: hgLWriteRow
hgLWriteRow.description: Setting this variable will alter the huntgroup table by setting every huntgroup in list to include outPortList. FORMAT: HuntgroupList OutportList Huntgroup is 0 to 31. Outport is 0 to 15 and 16. 16 will clear the huntgroup. List is NUMBER or NUMBER1-NUMBER2 where NUMBER1 < NUMBER2.

huntGroupOrderTable.name: huntGroupOrderTable
huntGroupOrderTable.description: This table holds all of the huntgroup order information for this switch. i.e. The order huntgroups are processed in when more than one huntgroup contends for the same output port. FORMAT: OutputPort HuntGroupList OutputPort is 0 to 15. Huntgroup is 0 to 31. List is an ordered list of huntgroups.

huntGroupOrderEntry.name: huntGroupOrderEntry
huntGroupOrderEntry.description: One record on an output port's huntgroup priority.

hgOrderIndex.name: hgOrderIndex
hgOrderIndex.description: The backplane slot number containing output port.

hgOrderList.name: hgOrderList
hgOrderList.description: An ordered list of an output port's huntgroup priority. FORMAT: OutputPort HuntGroupList OutputPort is 0 to 15. Huntgroup is 0 to 31. List is an ordered list of huntgroups.

hgOWriteRow.name: hgOWriteRow
hgOWriteRow.description: Setting this variable will alter the huntgroup order table. FORMAT: OutputPort HuntGroupList Output port is 0 to 15. Huntgroup is 0 to 31. Huntgroup must contain output port in its output port list. List is NUMBER or NUMBER1-NUMBER2 where NUMBER1 < NUMBER2.

hgSaveRestore.name: hgSaveRestore
hgSaveRestore.description: Writting a 1 saves all hunt group information on the switch. Writting a 2 restores all hunt group information on the switch.

routesSaveRestore.name: routesSaveRestore
routesSaveRestore.description: Writting a 1 saves all source/destination routes on the switch. Writting a 2 restores all source/destination routes on the switch.
